{"type":"message","id":"f989c1f2","parentId":"28041338","timestamp":"2026-02-12T19:16:06.939Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Analyzing File Paths**\n\nI've determined that `waxpeer.json` uses absolute file paths, specifically referencing directories like `C:\\Users\\west2\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs` and `C:\\Users\\west2\\.openclaw\\workspace`. The next step is to examine implications.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1770923766340_93","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# GitHub Audit Report: SACS-2026\n\n## 1. Typos in JSON Files\nThe following typos were detected in `.openclaw/agents/*.json`. These corrupt the skill names or paths.\n\n- **`engine.json`, `ops.json`, `sec.json`**:\n  - Found: `\\u0007gent-development` (Contains `BEL` control character).\n  - Expected: `agent-development`.\n- **`engine.json`, `ops.json`, `sec.json`, `sentinel.json`**:\n  - Found: `\\file-organizer`.\n  - Expected: `file-organizer` (Backslash suggests an escape sequence or path error).\n\n## 2. Logic Errors in `src/core/engine.py`\nThe `HybridEngine` class has critical flaws in its error handling logic.\n\n- **Blocking I/O in Async Loop**:\n  - The `handle_error` method uses `with open(..., \"a\")`, which is a blocking synchronous operation. This pauses the entire asyncio event loop, potentially causing heartbeats to timeout or other coroutines to freeze.\n- **Hardcoded Relative Path**:\n  - `LOG_AGENT_FILE = \"ERROR_LOG.md\"` is a relative path. If the engine is started from a subdirectory (e.g., `src/core/`), the log file will be created there instead of the workspace root, making it invisible to the `log` agent.\n\n## 3. \"Crutches\" (Hardcoded Paths & Incomplete Logic)\nSeveral implementations rely on environment-specific hardcoding that will break on other machines or user accounts.\n\n- **Absolute Paths in Agent Docs**:\n  - All 13 agents contain hardcoded absolute paths:\n    - `C:\\Users\\west2\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs`\n    - `C:\\Users\\west2\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\...`\n  - **Risk**: These paths are specific to user `west2` and will fail for any other user or if the workspace is moved.\n- **Hardcoded Usernames**:\n  - `log.json`: \"Output a concise 'DIAGNOSIS' report to **Arkady**\".\n  - `ops.json`: \"Alert **Arkady**/Admin\".\n  - **Risk**: Hardcoding a specific human name makes the agent less reusable.\n- **Conceptual Placeholders**:\n  - `net.json` refers to `src/utils/api_client.py` as \"(conceptual)\". If this file is missing, the agent cannot perform its scope.\n\n## 4. Consistency Check\n- **Documentation Links**:\n  - All agents *do* have documentation links, but they are consistently **incorrect** due to the absolute path issue mentioned above.\n  - The new skills (`sw-data-visualizer`, `neural-memory`, `openclaw-github-assistant`) are consistently added to all agents, but again with absolute paths.\n\n## Conclusion\n**Status: CHANGES REQUESTED**\nThe `dev` branch contains breaking typos (control characters in JSON), blocking code in the async engine, and environment-hardcoded paths that prevent portable deployment. \n**Do not merge until these issues are resolved.**\n","file_path":"github_audit_report.md"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":""}],"api":"google-generative-ai","provider":"google","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":18384,"output":986,"cacheRead":16514,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19370,"cost":{"input":0.036767999999999995,"output":0.011832,"cacheRead":0.0033028000000000003,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0519028}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1770923754712}}
